The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, November 24, 2004 

 Minister blasts police

 Calcutta, Nov. 23: Agriculture minister Kamal Guha, who is known to embarrass the government at intervals, today charged police with teaming up with criminals to malign the administration.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee holds charge of the police department. Guha said: ?I have information that some policemen are in league with those involved in gambling, illicit liquor trade, online lottery business and several other anti-social activities.? 

 The Forward Bloc leader also accused the government of ignoring his party?s repeated complaints.




